				<div class="postbody">
				Everyone who protested the invasion gets called a traitor. Or gets accused somehow of being against the morale of the soldiers. When you are busy catching up on your readings, look for those themes in silencing those against the war. Also observe how anti-war protests get disappeared from the main stream news, and how pro-war demonstrations get splashed all over the news. You saw it coming in the last gulf war, when 100,000 people at an anti-war protest get exactly the same coverage as 20 people at a pro-war protest. Watch how domestic terrorists vanish from the news, while external terrorists are all over the news.
<br />

<br />
Also watch how the patriot act is used to silence dissent.
<br />

<br />
Watch the upcoming rhetoric for the election: the rethuglicans will be framing the issue as "a vote against bush = a vote for binladen." Read the goering quote again and you will start to see where the "bush=hitler" meme comes from.<br />
