				you people have totally derailed dinian's thread so i only think its fair that i attempt to get it back on track, basically screw GW.
<br />

<br />
Herman Goering had it right on the money.  We elect leaders to do our thinking for us and dont take the time from our own busy lives to see whats going on around us so that when all of a sudden the people we elected to make sure our happy lil home stays the way it is come on tv and tell us so and so is threatening our way of life before we have a chance to question it we're already thinkin "someone should go over there and teach him a thing or two!".  yes i'm stereotyping, but as a whole that is the way the we think.  it's the way most people around the world think.  
<br />

<br />
as long as martha and bob get to raise lil sarah and johnny up right without too much interferance from the outside world everything is peachy keen, and there is no reason to flip to cnn or msnbc as opposed to tgif or trl or whatever cute set of letters people watch today.
<br />

<br />
it was this way all throughout history, and it is still like this today.  we've just gotten better at deluding ourselves into thinking we're informed.
<br />

<br />
a couple of my favorite bs lines were hitler's excuse that poland tried to invade germany, and us battle cry in spanish-american war "remember the maine".
<br />

<br />
anyways you can resume arguing about how bush is your bane/savior again.  just thought i'd put my 2cp in on din's topic.<br />
